{
  "stem": "19895.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As I--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As I did say, you know, the daily routine of this location, Harka-- terrible name to remember-- it was, if one remembers what was it like, and I think atrocities, how they treated us, were daily routines that you were brutalized physically as you were walking by on those trenches, the location where we had the labor which we had to perform.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were always reminded of being Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were treated like the scum of the world.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as I remember-- I don't really recall as much of individual scenes of brutality.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because that was daily routine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "To be shoved and pushed and hit, and-- and-- and-- and-- and blood flowing because they poked you a little bit with the bayonets of the guns.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We accepted that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The main thing was to survive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the general feeling of dehumanization, the way we felt, it is indescribable.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I am jumping to today-- present day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why am I telling that, why am I telling that now?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I am telling that on the urging of my-- urging of my daughters.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my wife, who said that you have to do that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I want to do it today, between-- just happens to be between Rosh Hashanah and Yom Kippur, the Jewish high holidays.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I owe that, that I am telling this now, to-- to tell what I went through, to tell it for an eyewitness who tells and knows what went on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I never done that until now.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, at my workplace, hardly anybody knew in the hospital that I am a Holocaust survivor.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That terminology-- Holocaust survivor-- you know, it's-- kind of puts everything into one cover.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's a good term and a bad term as well.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
